<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.55985>
    bibo:endPage "182" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" ;
    bibo:startPage "151" ;
    bibo:volume "67" ;
    dc:creator "Kipling, Will" ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "Phylogeny and classification of the genus-group taxa of Loxandrina (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Abacetini)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.55985.figures4-7>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.55985.figures8-11>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.55985.figure1>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.55985.figure3> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.55985.figures4-7>
    dc:description "Figures 4 - 7. Habitus. 4. Oxycrepis (Loxandrus) recta (Say); 5. O. strigomeroides (Straneo); 6. O. & nbsp; elnae (Allen); 7. O. (Adrimus) rasutulis Will." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448258" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.55985.figures8-11>
    dc:description "Figures 8 - 11. Habitus. 8. Oxycrepis (s. str.) cordata (Tschitscherine); 9. O. (Stolonis) tapiai (Will); 10. O. (Metoncidus) epiphyta (Will) (holotype); 11. Pediomorphus planiusculus Chaudoir." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448251" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.55985.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Phylogeny of Loxandrina inferred from a Bayesian analysis of the combined dataset (analysis 3). Numbers at nodes are posterior probability values (PP). Stars at nodes mark clades found in a parsimony optimality analysis using the morphology partition. Diamonds at nodes mark recognized genera and subgenera inferred from a Bayesian analysis of the sequence data partition (analysis 2)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448247" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/dez.67.55985.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Protarsomeres and metepimera. Male left tibia and protarsomeres: A. Oxycrepis (Loxandrus) recta (Say). Asymmetrically expanded, as in typical many Loxandrina species; B. Oxycrepis (Adrimus) gebi Will narrow, symmetrically, slightly expanded. Metepimera, left side: C. Oxycrepis (Loxandrus) recta. Large, elongate, apically rounded form, as in typical Loxandrina species. Black outline added to emphasize shape; D. Oxycrepis (Adrimus) rasutulis Will. Rectangular, narrow, truncate form, black outline added to emphasize shape. Drawings of alternative metepimera shapes: E. short, apically rounded form; F. narrowly triangular, truncate form." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448249" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

